== <div style="background-color:rgba(173, 216, 230, 0.75); color: white; margin:1em; font-family:Futura text-shadow: 0 0 15px #0a7e8c, 0 0 35px Black, 0 0 40px Grey; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center; border-radius:4px;"><font size="6">Entities</font></div> ==
==Tornadoes==
{{Entity Class|Agg=2|Int=2|Dan=5|no=74|Hab=Windy or outdoor levels}}
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 553 tornado.png|caption=“A picture of a tornado during the Blue phase”.}}
'''[[Entity 74]]''' or Tornadoes, are very common within Level 553, primarily during the Blue phase and sometimes during the Green phase. During these periods, large supercell storms may develop across the open fields, producing powerful and unpredictable tornadoes. These tornadoes are extremely strong and have been estimated to reach EF5 intensity, with wind speeds exceeding 201 mph. Such powerful storms are capable of ripping trees out of the ground and leaving deep scars across the terrain.

The tornadoes can appear in many different shapes and sizes. Some may form as extremely large wedge tornadoes that span a significant portion of the horizon, while others may appear as multi vortex tornadoes containing several smaller rotating funnels within the main circulation. These storms often move unpredictably across the level’s open landscape, making them particularly dangerous to wanderers caught in the open.

It's unknown how long these Tornadoes live but is estimated at around 20 minutes, to an hour.

== <div style="background-color:rgba(173, 216, 230, 0.75); color: white; margin:1em; font-family:Futura text-shadow: 0 0 15px #0a7e8c, 0 0 35px Black, 0 0 40px Grey; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center; border-radius:4px;"><font size="6">Colonies And Outposts</font></div> ==
Due to the extreme weather conditions, no colonies or outposts have been successfully established within the level.
== <div style="background-color:rgba(173, 216, 230, 0.75); color: white; margin:1em; font-family:Futura text-shadow: 0 0 15px #0a7e8c, 0 0 35px Black, 0 0 40px Grey; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center; border-radius:4px;"><font size="6">Entrances And Exits</font></div> ==
===Entrances===
*'''A white door found on [[Level 66]] may lead here if noclipped through.
*'''Noclipping through an oak tree on [[Level 630]] has a high chance of leading here.
*'''Breaking a vase on [[Level 29]] may lead to this level.
*'''Removing all the leaves from a tall plant on [[Level 63]] may cause one to enter this level.

===Exits===
*'''Climbing a tall oak tree may lead to [[Level 110]].
*'''Being sucked into a tornado has a very small chance of leading to [[Level 9.99]].
*'''Staring directly into the sun for 5 minutes may cause one to noclip into [[Level 46]].

